==English==

===Etymology===
Chef [[w:Auguste Escoffier|Auguste Escoffier]] at the [[w:Savoy Hotel|Savoy Hotel]] in London in 1892 or 1893 created the dish for, and named it after, Australian opera singer [[w:Nellie Melba|Nellie Melba]].

===Noun===
'''[[Peach]] Melba'''

# (''gastronomy'') '''Peach Melba''': classic French dessert, combing peaches and raspberry sauce accompanied with vanilla ice cream.

